        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 4:58PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Keota, or 33 miles northwest of Fort Morgan, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Raymer, Keota and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If a tornado is spotted seek shelter inside a sturdy building.</instruction>
